<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="quorum_sensing">Quorum Sensing</a> - The ability of an organism to detect population density of others and or a <a href="#molecule">molecule</a>. The canonical quorum sensing system is the AHL-Lux system first described in <em>Aliivibrio fischeri</em> (formerly classified as <em>Vibrio fischeri</em>). Quorum sensing systems have been co-opted by <a href="#synthetic_biology">synthetic biologists</a> to engineer cell-to-cell communication systems.